(http://www.platts.com/quote.shtml)


ENERGY INSIGHT:
(for Platts Premium Customers)

Mark-to-market coming under scrutiny
Enron Corp's supernova-like flameout has drawn attention to the inherent quirks
of mark-to-market accounting. While Enron certainly was a mark-to-market abuser,
the question now is how to prevent other companies from abusing hypothetical
future contract values and booking spurious cash flow in the present.
(http://www.einsight.com)


